news.title: Don't compel Jewar farmers to sell land: Allahabad HC to Noida administration
news.para: The court, however, made it clear that the state authorities could acquire the land by following procedures prescribed by the law.

news.title: Chandigarh: F&CC gives nod to 17 more construction & demolition collection points
news.para: During the monthly meeting, the committee discussed and approved multiple agenda items. The meeting was held under the supervision of mayor Anup Gupta and was attended by elected members and senior administrative and engineering officers of the civic body.

news.title: HUDCO inks pact with Gujarat to invest Rs 14,500 crore to finance housing, urban infra projects
news.para: ​The state government intends for overall development of Gujarat by implementing various housing and infrastructure projects, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Pune: Auction of 50 commercial properties finalized for January 2024
news.para: Before auction, the civic body explores different options to recover property tax like issuance of notices, attaching the property and sealing it for a temporary period.

news.title: Industrial plots to cost 12% more in Greater Noida
news.para: So, plots measuring up to 1,000sqm (quarter of an acre) will be available at the rate of Rs 29,238 per sqm. Similarly, land parcels from 1,001-20,000sqm will cost upwards of Rs 23,975. There has been no change in the price of plots bigger than 20,000sqm.

news.title: Panchkula: Self-certify property to get 15% tax rebate
news.para: MC commissioner Sachin Gupta said the urban local bodies (ULB) have decided to give rebate on property tax in the current financial year 2023-2024.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 25,000 properties under tax net in six months; adds Rs 46 crore in revenue
news.para: Out of these 25,000, 60% of the properties are from the two divisions alone: Panchavati and Cidco. NMC officials said that the civic body will get additional Rs 46 crore revenue through these properties.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir administration approves increased subsidy under PMAY
news.para: ​Jammu and Kashmir's Administrative Council (AC), during a meeting chaired by Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha on Tuesday night, approved an enhancement of subsidy to Rs 70,326 from the current Rs 16,666 for people eligible for the BLC of PMAY(U).

news.title: Maharashtra education minister seeks action against housing societies polluting river
news.para: The minister held a meeting in this regard on Tuesday with PCMC and other authorities concerned. The meeting followed the state government’s promise to keep rivers clean during the winter session of the state assembly.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM hints at probe into Wakad land 'TDR scam'
news.para: Pawar said he had checked the documents about the deal with several retired officers and they expressed scope of doubt for irregularities.

news.title: App to approve house maps up to 100 meter in Haridwar
news.para: Vice chairman of HRDA, Anshul Singh, told TOI, “Maps under 100 metres are being approved online through the ‘UDAY’ app and our teams are delivering the approved maps at applicants’ home to make people aware about the app.”

news.title: Uttarakhand likely to tighten law on land sale to outsiders
news.para: But local residents are now demanding that power to buy land even in municipal areas be curtailed to 250 sqm and a complete ban be imposed on sale of land in rural areas.

news.title: Noida, Greater Noida authority paves way to restart stuck housing projects
news.para: In their board meeting on Tuesday, both the authorities gave final approval which will allow builders to take benefit of zero period, more time for payment of dues, permission to mortgage among others.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' shares make disappointing market debut; settle with over 7% discount
news.para: ​A​t the BSE, the stock made its debut at Rs 343.80, a discount of 4.5 per cent from the issue price. During the day, shares of the company plunged 10 per cent to Rs 323.95 before settling at Rs 334.30, down by 7.13 per cent.

news.title: Delhi High Court allows retired BSF employees to complete stuck housing project
news.para: The members had entered into an agreement with the builder in 2006 for the purchase of 266 flats in the project for Rs 65 crore, and the flats were to be handed over by June, 2010.

news.title: MahaRERA recovers nearly Rs 140 crore as homebuyers' compensation through warrants
news.para: The authority has issued 1,123 warrants so far this year to recover nearly Rs 764 crore from developers for the delay in the handing over of the apartments, with a warning to freeze their bank accounts and attach assets.

news.title: Jaipur zonal master plan for seven eco-sensitive zones released
news.para: An official stated, “The Zonal Master Plans of eco-sensitive zones address all key development issues, including land use, infrastructure, and transportation, with a primary focus on ecology, environment, and wildlife.”
